Embattled former eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede has been sworn in at the KZN legislature. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal says embattled former eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede is innocent until proven guilty. Gumede has been sworn in as an MPL in the KZN legislature. READ: Senior Free State officials to appear in court She is still being investigated for corruption and fraud. ANC KZN's provincial spokesperson Nhlakanipho Ntombela says Gumede has been removed from the eThekwini metro in order to ensure the stability of that municipality and utilising her experience in other levels of the organisation.  #ZandileGumede Former @eThekwiniM Mayor #ZandileGumede has been sworn in as a member of the @kZNLegislature. #eNCA pic.twitter.com/hD9ZcbTQkF   